column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: Control clear. No ice in channel or at control. Some patches of snow and ice in shaded areas.
column14: Excellent quality Flowtracker2 wading measurement collected approximately 50m upstream of gauge. No QA/QC issues to note. Water level stable during measurement. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Invalid stage record upon arrival to site due to equipment malfunction with FTS bubbler. Replaced FTS bubbler with a new unit. Installed 40m OTT PLS 500 inside an OTT junction box and buried deep in channel along left bank. OTT junction box buried deep into the streambed and covered with rocks and cobbles. Additional boulders added to OTT junction box to secure in channel. Armored line armored with large boulders and trenched from the bank, up the hill to the gauge. OTT zip tied, covered in landscape fabric and secured within junction box using OTT pressure fittings and surrounded by gravels and small cobbles. An additional layer of landscape fabric encloses the gravels and cobbles around the OTT. Set an averaging time of 10seconds for OTT & Bubbler for channel conditions (riffles). OTT and Bubbler rail tie situated in a calm location. Mid-section
GC: 0.000 Surge: 0.005  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Found (FD)

column14: Discharge Grade: B Discharge Remarks: Q uncertainty = 2.8% (ISO). Good measurement. Edge ice only. Chop and wade measurement. Control Condition Remarks: Edge ice at riffle control and throughout channel (1-2m width from edge). The ice appears partially bridged above water level so may minimize the overall backwater affect from ice. No anchor ice observed during visit. Slush flowing on water surface (~0.05 to 0.1m dia.).  MGH has had sensor reset applied at upload (1.148 + 0.000) Sources:eHSN v1.3.2
Source:eHSN v1.3.2 Sensor Reset Correction of -0.002

Discharge Remarks: Some minimal slush began to flow during measurement period as sun rising and warming temperatures (slush dia ~0.1m). Control Condition Remarks: Very slight ice surface layer buildup on edges at control but expect negligable backwater affect currently. Loose gravel scattered throughout riffle control between all voids. This gravel likely moves at higher flows possibly changing control.  5.00 metres below gauge MGH has had sensor reset applied at upload (1.100 + 0.000) Sources:eHSN v1.3.2
